					<head>Liturgy</head>
					<msContents class="lccn.loc.gov/n79090052" rend="visible">
						<summary>A service book according to the Yemenite rite.</summary>
						<textLang mainLang="he" otherLangs="jrb"> </textLang>
						<msItem n="0" rend="visible" class="lccn.loc.gov/n79090052">
							<locus from="1r" to="111v"/>
							<title xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">Sidur</title>
							<title xml:lang="he">סדור</title>
							<colophon xml:lang="he">שושרח . יום ה' כח' באב שנת <date calendar="Seleucid">בנב</date> במאתא צנעא והכותב קל הקלים <name type="person" role="scribe">שלום בן זכריה בן פינחס הכהן</name> ת'נ'צ'ב'ה'.<locus n="110v"/>
							</colophon>
							<note>
								<p>The text is provided with the superlinear punctuation, with the exception of the book of Lamentations (folio 28r sqq.) and the biblical verses at the head of the services, which have the sublinear punctuation. </p>
								<p>The liturgical directions are partly in Arabic in Hebrew characters and partly in Hebrew.</p>
								<p>The services are very largely only indicated by directions.</p>
							</note>
						</msItem>
						<msItem rend="">
							<locus from="2r" to="10r"/>
							<title xml:lang="en">Services for week-days</title>
						</msItem>
						<msItem rend="">
							<locus from="10r" to="18v"/>
							<title xml:lang="en">Services for Sabbath</title>
							<note>
								<p>Tefilat lel Shabat, folio 10r; shaḥarit, folio 10v; musaf, folio 12r; minḥah, folio 12r; tefilat motse Shabat, folio 17v.</p>
							</note>
						</msItem>
						<msItem rend="">
							<locus from="18v" to="19v"/>
							<title xml:lang="en">Services for rosh ḥodesh</title>
						</msItem>
						<msItem rend="">
							<locus from="19v" to="26v"/>
							<title xml:lang="en">Services for Pesaḥ</title>
							<note>
								<p>Tefilat lele Pesaḥ, folio 19v; seder ha-῾asiyah, folio 20r; shaḥarit, folio 24r; musaf, folio 25r; tefilat ḥulo shel Pesaḥ, folio 26r; tefilat yom shevi῾i shel Pesaḥ, folio 26r.</p>
							</note>
						</msItem>
						<msItem rend="">
							<locus from="26r" to="27r"/>
							<title xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">Tefilat ḥag Shavu῾ot</title>
							<note>
								<p>Includes all the services of the feast.</p>
							</note>
						</msItem>
						<msItem rend="">
							<locus from="27r" to="27v"/>
							<title xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">Tefilat ta῾aniyot</title>
						</msItem>
						<msItem rend="">
							<locus from="27v" to="32v"/>
							<title xml:lang="en">Services for Tish῾ah be-av</title>
							<note>
								<p>The book of Lamentations begins on folio 28r. </p>
							</note>
						</msItem>
						<msItem rend="">
							<locus from="32v" to="35v"/>
							<title xml:lang="en">Services for Rosh ha-Shanah</title>
							<filiation>Cf the contents of Or 2227, folio 28r.</filiation>
						</msItem>
						<msItem rend="">
							<locus from="35v" to="38r"/>
							<title xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">Services for Yom Kipur</title>
						</msItem>
						<msItem rend="">
							<locus from="38r" to="47v"/>
							<title xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">Tefilat ḥag Sukot</title>
						</msItem>
						<msItem rend="">
							<locus from="47v" to="50r"/>
							<title xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">Seder ha-῾asiyah bi-shemonat yeme Ḥanukah</title>
							<note>
								<p>Megilat bene Ḥasmonai begins on folio 48v.</p>
							</note>
						</msItem>
						<msItem rend="">
							<locus from="50r" to="50v"/>
							<title xml:lang="en">Services for Purim</title>
						</msItem>
						<msItem rend="">
							<locus from="50v" to="51v"/>
							<title xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">Tseloah almiyat</title>
						</msItem>
						<msItem rend="">
							<locus from="51v" to="57r"/>
							<title xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">Seliḥot le-lele ashmurot</title>
						</msItem>
						<msItem rend="">
							<locus from="57r" to="86v"/>
							<title xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">Seliḥot le-el raḥamim</title>
							<filiation>Cf the content of Or 2389, XVI.</filiation>
						</msItem>
						<msItem rend="">
							<locus from="86v" to="90r"/>
							<title xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">Seder ῾avodah</title>
							<author>
								<persName xml:lang="en" key="http://viaf.org/viaf/90633023">Ibn Ezra, Abraham ben Meïr, 1089-1164</persName>
								<persName xml:lang="he" key="http://viaf.org/viaf/90633023">אבן עזרא, אברהם בן מאיר, 1089-1164</persName>
							</author>
						</msItem>
						<msItem rend="">
							<locus from="90r" to="96r"/>
							<title xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">Berakhot</title>
						</msItem>
						<msItem rend="">
							<locus from="96r" to="103v"/>
							<title xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">῾Ibur ha-shanim</title>
							<note>
								<p>The calculations are carried through to the year 5536. Then follow general rules on the different kinds of years.</p>
							</note>
						</msItem>
						<msItem rend="">
							<locus from="103v" to="107r"/>
							<title xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">Nusaḥ ha-ketubot, ha-giṭin ṿeha-sheṭarot</title>
							<note>
								<p>The forms of documents, partly accompanied by dinim in Arabic in Hebrew characters.</p>
							</note>
						</msItem>
						<msItem rend="">
							<locus from="107r" to="111v"/>
							<title xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">Liturgical pieces</title>
							<note>
								<p>Includes Tokhaḥot u-vaḳashot and Shirot ṿe-tishbaḥot.</p>
							</note>
						</msItem>
					</msContents>
					<physDesc rend="visible">
						<p>Paper codex of the 18th century.</p>
						<objectDesc form="codex">
							<supportDesc material="chart">
								<support>Paper.</support>
								<extent>111 folios <dimensions unit="mm" type="leaf">
										<height>320</height>
										<width>210</width>
									</dimensions>
									<dimensions type="written" unit="mm">
										<height>260</height>
										<width>160</width>
									</dimensions>
								</extent>
								<foliation>
									<p>111 folios (+ 3 unfoliated paper flyleaves at the beginning and at the end).</p>
								</foliation>
								<collation>
									<p>Quires of originally 8 leaves each.</p>
								</collation>
								<condition>
									<p>Leaves stuck on paper (modern restoration).</p>
									<p>Folios damaged at the beginning and at the end.</p>
								</condition>
							</supportDesc>
							<layoutDesc>
								<layout columns="1 2" ruledLines="29" writtenLines="29">
									<p>Uniform layout. </p>
									<p>Visible mastara ruling.</p>
									<p>Initial words written in larger characters.</p>
									<p>Leaf catchwords on every verso.</p>
									<p>Numerous marginal notes and additions.</p>
								</layout>
							</layoutDesc>
						</objectDesc>
						<handDesc hands="2">
							<summary>Yemenite semi-cursive script, punctuated, of the 18th century. <name type="person" role="scribe">Shalom Zekhariah ben Pinḥas ha-Kohen</name>: inscribed, folio 110v.</summary>
							<handNote script="Hebrew" scope="major"/>
						</handDesc>
						<additions>
							<p>Folio 111 contains calendar tables for the years 5587-5605, dated <date calendar="Seleucid">2137</date> (<date calendar="Gregorian">1826</date>).</p>
						</additions>
